[2] Lethal yellowing - Mozambique
Date: Fri 3 Sep 2010
Source: Macauhub/El Pais [edited]
<http://www.macauhub.com.mo/en/news.php?ID=10079>


Lethal yellowing affects 110 000 hectares
-----------------------------------------
Lethal yellowing disease of coconut palms in Mozambique's Zambezia province
is affecting the survival of residents in some of the province's districts.
Authorities said that an area of 110 000 hectares [about 272 000 acres] was
affected by the disease, with a level of infestation of between 22 and 28
per cent of the total area.

Over 70 000 diseased palms had been cut down and replaced by over 100 000
saplings. According to the Zambezia provincial government, the new palms
seem to be resistant to the disease, particularly the variety that was
imported from the Ivory Coast.

In 2009, the Millennium Challenge Account provided USD 17.4 million to
fight the disease over 5 years. 15 per cent of the Zambezia population is
dependent on coconut palms for their survival.

[Additional news story: <http://allafrica.com/stories/201009010080.html>]

